-- Citrix Systems Jumps to Highest in Nine Years as Analysts Recommend Stock
-- Stephanie Borise
-- 2010-07-29T13:55:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/citrix-systems-shares-jump-to-highest-in-nine-years-after-analyst-upgrades.html

          
          
             Citrix Systems Inc., a maker of
networking software, jumped to the highest price in nine years
after the stock was upgraded.  
 The shares surged $7.56, or 16 percent, to $54.89 at 9:36
a.m. in New York, and earlier reached $55.50, the highest since
June 2000.  
 The stock was raised to “outperform” from
“neutral” at Robert Baird & Co. and to “neutral” from
“underperform” at Cowen & Co.  
 Citrix yesterday said its fiscal third quarter earnings
excluding some items would be between 48 cents and 49 cents a
share. An average of 27 estimates from analysts polled by
Bloomberg forecast earnings of 48 cents a share.        
